One of the big selling points of Preact is that one can use all components that were originally written for React. There is no need to convert them to Preact or anything. This is typically done via aliasing `react` and `react-dom` to `preact/compat`:

```js
// webpack.config.js
module.exports = {
  // ...rest of your webpack config
  resolve: {
    alias: {
      react: 'preact/compat',
      'react-dom': 'preact/compat'
    }
  }
};
```

